		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Mass surveillance</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Closed.circuit.camera.arp.750pix.jpg" class="image" title="A closed-circuit television camera."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Closed.circuit.camera.arp.750pix.jpg/300px-Closed.circuit.camera.arp.750pix.jpg" width="300" height="220" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Closed.circuit.camera.arp.750pix.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A <a href="/wiki/Closed-circuit_television" title="Closed-circuit television">closed-circuit television</a> camera.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Mass surveillance</b> is the pervasive <a href="/wiki/Surveillance" title="Surveillance">surveillance</a> of an entire population, or a substantial fraction thereof.</p>
<p>Modern governments today commonly perform mass surveillance of their citizens, explaining that they believe that it is necessary to protect them from dangerous groups such as <a href="/wiki/Terrorists" title="Terrorists" class="mw-redirect">terrorists</a>, <a href="/wiki/Criminals" title="Criminals" class="mw-redirect">criminals</a>, or political <a href="/wiki/Subversives" title="Subversives" class="mw-redirect">subversives</a> and to maintain <a href="/wiki/Social_control" title="Social control">social control</a>.</p>
<p>Mass surveillance has been widely criticized on several grounds such as violations of <a href="/wiki/Privacy" title="Privacy">privacy</a> rights, illegality, and for preventing political and social freedoms, which some fear will ultimately lead to a <a href="/wiki/Totalitarian_state" title="Totalitarian state" class="mw-redirect">totalitarian state</a> where political dissent is crushed by <a href="/wiki/COINTELPRO" title="COINTELPRO">COINTELPRO</a>-like programs.</p>
